● intro  {

  The  LINE  plugin  will  have  a flux file as well. It's going to be used to
  generate highlight instructions  for the coloring of both the statusline and
  the tabline.

  The  syntax  will follow the same idea of the one used in the NVPM plugin.
  Although the flux#vars feature is  yet  to  be implemented, it's going to be
  used  to  define  color  variables and use them throughout  the  flux  file.

  Those files will carry the extention *.iris, which foretells the future iris
  plugin.

}
● syntax {

The following is an example of a flux file made for the LINE plugin:

--------------- ayu.iris -----------------------------
  file ~/.nvpm/line/ayu.vim

  background dark {
    group LineFill = *Normal
    group LineProj = 0x000 *Title.guifg
    group LineGitS = *DiffAdded
    group LineGitM = *SpellBad
    group LineGitC = *Normal
    group LineMode = *WildMenu
    group linecurr {
      mode normal   = 0x000 0x0f0
      mode insert   = 0x000 0xf00
      mode replace  = 0x000 0xf00
      mode visual   = *Visual.guibg
      mode cmdline  = 0x000 *Title.guibg
      mode terminal = 0x000 *Operator.guibg
    }
    group lineinac {
      mode normal   = *linecurrmoden.guibg *linefill.guibg
      mode insert   = *linecurrmodei.guibg *linefill.guibg
      mode replace  = *linecurrmoder.guibg *linefill.guibg
      mode visual   = *linecurrmodev.guibg *linefill.guibg
      mode cmdline  = *linecurrmodec.guibg *linefill.guibg
      mode terminal = *linecurrmodet.guibg *linefill.guibg
    }
  }
------------------------------------------------------

}
